In [42]:
#diff b/w KNN and K means clustering
#1.)
#   KNN is used for classification and regression
#   K means is used for clustering problems
#
#2.) 
#   KNN is supervised algorithm
#   K means is unsupervised algorithm
#
#3.)
#   to taring KNN, we nead a dataset with all the data points having class labels
#   For training K means, we no need any such information

# 4.) We use KNN to predict the class label or new points
#     we use K means to find patterns in a given dataset by grouping datapoints
#     into clusters
